{"article_id":"MmzmCh1pHAADyhrQ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Hiring was surprisingly strong in October ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"while the unemployment rate ticked higher ,","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"according to a report","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"released just four days before the presidential election .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"The economy added 171,000 jobs in October ,","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"and unemployment inched up to 7.9 % , from 7.8 % in September ,","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"the Labor Department said Friday .","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"Obama 's economy","depth":2},{"id":8,"text":"View photos","depth":3},{"id":9,"text":"A look at where the economy stood","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"when Obama took office","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"and what 's changed since .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"Economists","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"surveyed by CNNMoney","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"had expected employers to add 125,000 positions ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"so the boost in hiring was mostly seen as a positive surprise .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Superstorm Sandy ,","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"which devastated the northeastern part of the U.S. this week ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"had no impact on the report","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"since the survey was taken earlier in the month ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"the Labor Department said .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Another good sign was that job growth in recent months was even stronger","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"than originally reported .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"The number of positions","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"added in August and September","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"were revised sharply higher ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"adding a combined 84,000 more jobs","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"than first thought .","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"`` We are again seeing a quickening in the rate of hiring , ''","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"said Heather Boushey , senior economist at the left-leaning Center for American Progress .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"`` It 's moving in the right direction . ''","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"However , the pace of hiring has not regained the force","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"it had in January and February ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"when more than 250,000 jobs were added each month .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"The rise in unemployment was expected by economists ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"and was mainly because more people joined the labor force .","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"Some economists believe","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"that September 's drop in unemployment encouraged those out of work to reenter the labor force .","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"The job gains were spread across varying industries ,","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"with the entire private sector adding 184,000 people to the payroll .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"Professional and business services added 51,000 positions ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"while health care employment rose by 31,000 .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"The construction sector continued to bring on employees ,","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"adding 17,000 jobs last month .","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"Retail and leisure and hospitality also boosted payrolls .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"But government employers took a step back ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"shedding 13,000 jobs after several strong months of gains .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Manufacturing was little changed","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"and mining lost 9,000 jobs .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"`` A few more people are working ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"but they are not making any more , ''","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"said Keith Hembre , chief economist at Nuveen Asset Management .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"The report , the last before Tuesday 's election , will likely be picked apart by politicians as well as economists .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"September 's report ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"which showed an unexpected drop in the unemployment rate ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"prompted an outcry from Republican supporters ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"including Jack Welch ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"claiming","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"the figure had been manipulated .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"The monthly jobs report has taken on increased importance","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"as the nation struggles to recover from the economic downturn .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Roughly 12.3 million people remain unemployed ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"40.6 % of whom have been so for more than six months .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"And presidential candidates Barack Obama and Mitt Romney are centering much of the campaigns on who can create more jobs .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"Obama touted the rosy report on the campaign trail Friday ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"noting","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"that employers have picked up hiring lately .","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"`` This morning we learned","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"that companies hired more workers in October than at any time in the last eight months , ''","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"he said in Ohio .","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"Romney , meanwhile , swiftly issued a statement","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"the report was `` a sad reminder","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"that the economy is at a virtual standstill . ''","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"He noted","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"the jobless rate is higher","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"than it was","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"when Obama took office .","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"In January 2009 , the unemployment rate was 7.8 % .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"While many industries are adding jobs ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"the current tepid pace of growth is not enough","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"to climb out of the jobs hole ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"economists said .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Companies remain hesitant to boost payrolls .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"One of their main worries ?","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"How the president and Congress deal with the looming fiscal cliff .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"`` The broader economy is still just limping along , ''","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"said Bill Dunkelberg , chief economist for the National Federation of Independent Business .","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"`` We do n't really see any major pickup in job growth . ''","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":177,"left":95,"right":176,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":92,"right":94,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":90,"right":91,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":91,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":93,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":176,"left":7,"right":175,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":175,"left":8,"right":174,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":174,"left":137,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":97,"right":136,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":97,"left":96,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":96,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":122,"right":135,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":105,"right":121,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":100,"right":104,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":99,"right":15,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"paren